So that by two o\rquote clock in the afternoon, Jimmy Johnson, who was \'85 he was the Village Overseer, rate collector, walked me down from Hope Town to Fort Willington, which is about a mile, to the District Commissioner\rquote 
s Office, although it was actually the Assistant District Commissioner, a very pleasant young Indian and wry, and I explained to him what I was doing, and so on.  And I finally got the train back to Georgetown that aft
ernoon, a good deal worse for wear!  But it seemed \'85 it seemed as though that had clinched the deal.  You know, I\rquote d been to a lot of other places before.  So within another week or two, I\rquote 
d decided to go there, and I moved in.  I had this little house that I rented, and got some minimalist furniture, and I spent a year there.  It was an extremely happy year, I must say.  No running water, no electric light.
