 and determined.  He was a lawyer, and he\rquote d been \'85 trained in law in London.  And after he finally negotiated his way into power, he became extremely ruthless, murderously ruthless!  I saw a little bit of him after that, but he was \'85
 always wary of me after that.  I did go to his house. \'85 When he became Prime Minister, before he became President, he had a house in the Botanic Gardens, that he called \'93The Residence\'94.  It was t
he epitome of ostentation.  I mean, every kind of whisky you could think of!  But I knew him particularly well through a friend of mine, who was his personal physician, called Frank Williams, who I had met while I was in Hope Town.  But I knew Burnham bef
ore I knew Frank Williams.  I knew him, I met him very soon after I first arrived in Guiana in 1951, and Jagan, and a lot of the younger radical Left-wing, fire-eating people!
